# Safir

Lightweight Vue 3 UI component library for Stravigor.

Props over composition. HTML + classes over component trees. Things that just work.


## Install

```bash
bun add @stravigor/safir
```

Peer dependencies:

```bash
bun add vue @heroicons/vue
```


## Usage

```ts
import { Button, Input, Card, Alert, useToast } from '@stravigor/safir'
```

Or import individual components:

```ts
import Button from '@stravigor/safir/components/Button'
```


## Philosophy

Safir avoids deeply nested sub-component trees. Instead, components use props and slots.

```html
<!-- Safir way -->
<Alert title="Payment failed" variant="destructive" show-icon>
  <p>Please verify your billing information.</p>
</Alert>

<Card title="Team Members" description="Manage access.">
  <ul><li>Alice</li><li>Bob</li></ul>
  <template #footer>
    <Button variant="outline">Invite</Button>
  </template>
</Card>

<Input v-model="email" label="Email" :error="errors.email" :icon="EnvelopeIcon" />
```

Rules:
- A component can have at most 1-3 sub-components in its group
- Use HTML and Tailwind classes inside slots
- Props for data, slots for content


## Components

### Foundation

| Component | Key Props | Slots |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Button | variant, size, disabled, loading, type | default |
| Badge | variant | default |
| Input | v-model, label, error, icon, type, placeholder | - |
| Textarea | v-model, label, error, rows, placeholder | - |
| Label | for, required | default |
| Card | title, description | default, #footer |
| Spinner | size | - |
| Divider | label | - |
| Kbd | - | default |

### Form Controls

| Component | Key Props | Slots |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Checkbox | v-model, label, description, disabled | - |
| Radio | v-model, options[], label, disabled | - |
| Switch | v-model, label, description, disabled | - |
| Select | v-model, options[], label, error, placeholder | - |
| Progress | value, size, color, label, showValue | - |

### Display & Feedback

| Component | Key Props | Slots |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Alert | title, variant, showIcon, icon, dismissible | default |
| Avatar | src, alt, name, size | - |
| Skeleton | width, height, rounded | - |
| EmptyState | title, description, icon | default (actions) |
| ToastContainer | - | - |
| Tooltip | content, side | default (trigger) |

### Overlays & Navigation

| Component | Key Props | Slots |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Dialog | v-model, title, description | default, #footer |
| Drawer | v-model, title, description, side | default, #footer |
| Dropdown | items[], align | default (trigger) |
| Tabs | v-model, tabs[] | #tab-{key} |
| Breadcrumb | items[], separator | - |
| Pagination | v-model, total, perPage | - |

### Data Display

| Component | Key Props | Slots |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Table | columns[], rows[], sortBy, sortDir, striped | #cell-{key}, #empty |
| Collapse | v-model, title, icon | default |


## Examples

### Button

```html
<Button variant="destructive" size="sm" :loading="saving">Delete</Button>
```

### Input with label and error

```html
<Input v-model="email" type="email" label="Email" placeholder="you@example.com" :error="errors.email" />
```

### Select from options

```html
<Select v-model="country" label="Country" :options="['France', 'Madagascar', 'Japan']" />
```

### Radio group

```html
<Radio
  v-model="plan"
  label="Select plan"
  :options="[
    { value: 'free', label: 'Free', description: '10 projects' },
    { value: 'pro', label: 'Pro', description: 'Unlimited' }
  ]"
/>
```

### Alert

```html
<Alert title="Unable to process" variant="destructive" show-icon dismissible @dismiss="clear">
  <p>Please verify your billing information.</p>
</Alert>
```

### Dialog

```html
<Dialog v-model="open" title="Delete project?" description="This cannot be undone.">
  <p>All data will be permanently removed.</p>
  <template #footer>
    <Button variant="outline" @click="open = false">Cancel</Button>
    <Button variant="destructive" @click="remove">Delete</Button>
  </template>
</Dialog>
```

### Dropdown

```html
<Dropdown
  :items="[
    { label: 'Edit', icon: PencilIcon, action: 'edit' },
    { separator: true },
    { label: 'Delete', icon: TrashIcon, action: 'delete' }
  ]"
  @select="handleAction"
>
  <Button variant="ghost" size="icon">...</Button>
</Dropdown>
```

### Table

```html
<Table
  :columns="[
    { key: 'name', label: 'Name', sortable: true },
    { key: 'role', label: 'Role' },
    { key: 'actions', label: '', width: '80px' }
  ]"
  :rows="users"
  striped
>
  <template #cell-role="{ row }">
    <Badge :variant="row.role === 'admin' ? 'default' : 'secondary'">{{ row.role }}</Badge>
  </template>
  <template #cell-actions="{ row }">
    <Button variant="ghost" size="sm">Edit</Button>
  </template>
</Table>
```

### Tabs

```html
<Tabs v-model="tab" :tabs="[{ key: 'general', label: 'General' }, { key: 'security', label: 'Security' }]">
  <template #tab-general>
    <Input v-model="name" label="Name" />
  </template>
  <template #tab-security>
    <Input v-model="password" type="password" label="Password" />
  </template>
</Tabs>
```

### Toast

```ts
import { useToast } from '@stravigor/safir'

const { toast } = useToast()
toast({ title: 'Saved', description: 'Changes saved.', variant: 'success' })
```

Place `<ToastContainer />` once in your app root.


## Page Stubs

Safir ships ready-to-copy `.strav` page templates in `stubs/`. Copy them into your project's `resources/views/`, replace "MyApp" with your app name, done.

```bash
cp -r node_modules/@stravigor/safir/stubs/* resources/views/
```

### Layouts

| Layout | Extends | Purpose |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `layouts/base` | — | HTML5 shell, Tailwind CDN, Inter font, @islands() |
| `layouts/auth` | base | Centered card on zinc-50 background |
| `layouts/app` | base | Sidebar + topbar + main content area |
| `layouts/marketing` | base | Sticky navbar + footer |

### Auth Pages

All extend `layouts/auth`. Form fields match Bastion endpoints.

| Page | Route | Fields |
|------|-------|--------|
| `auth/login` | POST /login | email, password |
| `auth/register` | POST /register | name, email, password, password_confirmation |
| `auth/forgot-password` | POST /forgot-password | email |
| `auth/reset-password` | POST /reset-password | token, password, password_confirmation |
| `auth/verify-email` | POST /email/send | (resend button) |
| `auth/email-verified` | — | (success page) |
| `auth/two-factor` | POST /two-factor/challenge | code, recovery_code |

### App Pages

All extend `layouts/app`. Generic CRUD patterns — replace "items" with your resource.

| Page | Purpose | Template vars |
|------|---------|---------------|
| `app/dashboard` | Stats cards + recent items table | stats, recentItems, user |
| `app/list` | Table + empty state + pagination | title, items, total, page, totalPages |
| `app/show` | Detail page with breadcrumb + actions | item, fields |
| `app/form` | Create/edit form with validation errors | title, action, values, errors |
| `app/settings` | Profile + password + danger zone | user |

### Marketing Pages

All extend `layouts/marketing`.

| Page | Sections |
|------|----------|
| `marketing/landing` | Hero, 3-feature grid, pricing, CTA |
| `marketing/pricing` | 3-tier pricing cards, FAQ |

### Error Pages + Emails

| Page | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `errors/404` | Page not found |
| `errors/500` | Server error |
| `errors/403` | Access denied |
| `emails/welcome` | Welcome email with CTA |
| `emails/reset-password` | Password reset link |
| `emails/verify-email` | Email verification link |

### Partials

`partials/flash` — reusable error/success flash messages. Use via `@include('partials/flash')`.


## Stack

- Vue 3 with `<script setup lang="ts">`
- Tailwind CSS (zinc palette)
- class-variance-authority for variants
- clsx + tailwind-merge via cn()
- Heroicons (@heroicons/vue)
- No build step — raw .vue/.ts source, compiled by Bun at bundle time
